The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Ford, Emburey to arrive on Saturday

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Graham Ford and John Emburey will arrive in Chennai on Saturday morning to appear before the seven-man special committee empowered to pick the coach. It is possible that they will be arriving on the same flight from London. 

According to BCCI secretary Niranjan Shah, the meeting will take place in the evening. 

Shah also informed that the selection of the squads for the tours of Ireland and England will be held in Delhi on Tuesday. The selection committee will meet in Delhi at 5.30 pm on June 12 after the meeting of the working committee to choose the team for England and Ireland, Shah said. 




